# French Onion Soup

> #soup #leftovers

Preheat oven to 350.

- Baguette | 1 | Cubed and toasted

Let cubed breadcrumbs dry out on a baking sheet. (Optional)

Spread dried bread cubes onto a baking sheet and cook in the oven for 10 minutes, flipping halfway through.

- Onions | Spanish, 4 | Sliced
- Onions | Red, 1/2 | Sliced

Cook onions in a large pot over medium heat without butter until they begin to take on some color.

- Butter | Unsalted, 4 tbsp | 

Add butter and stir until melted and combined. Continue to cook onions until they are tender and starting to caramelize.

- Flour | 1 1/2 tbsp | 

Add flour and stir for 1 minute.

- Fresh Thyme | 1 tbsp | 
- Paprika | 1/4 tsp | 
- Better Than Bouillon | Beef, 3 tbsp | 
- Water | 5 cups | 
- Bay Leaf | 1 | 
- Balsamic Vinegar | 1 1/2 tbsp | 

Add thyme, paprika, bouillon, water, bay leaf and balsamic vinegar. Bring to a simmer and cook for 15 minutes.

- Black Pepper | to taste | 

Add black pepper and remove bay leaf.

- Gruyère |  | Shredded

Ladle soul into bowls, top with cubed toasted bread, and shredded Gruyère. Place on baking sheet under the broiler until cheese is melted and bubbly.
